209
00:18:02,176 --> 00:18:03,977
for a modern police facility.

210
00:18:04,758 --> 00:18:27,992
We worked very closely with Chief Sacco, Captain Clemente, Captain Fowler, Lieutenant Colarusso, Lieutenant Buckley, and now Chief Buckley on the program, which is taking that space need and developing plans that identified how we would build a new station to meet the physical space requirements of the police department.

211
00:18:29,152 --> 00:18:29,953
During that study,

212
00:18:30,580 --> 00:18:35,022
As the mayor mentioned, we looked at many different sites around the city.

213
00:18:36,122 --> 00:18:39,324
Many that have been named, many that have not been named.

214
00:18:40,084 --> 00:18:43,606
And that took us to practically every corner of the city.

215
00:18:44,486 --> 00:18:50,329
And we ultimately, as the mayor said, came back home here to the police station site.

216
00:18:55,355 --> 00:19:04,223
On this site we considered all options for the police department not just in the current academy location but what could we do on other areas of the site.

217
00:19:04,303 --> 00:19:19,496
We looked at parking, we looked at how this site integrated with the bus stop that was out front and all the other needs that would need to be solved as part of this project went forward including working carefully with city staff

218
00:19:20,236 --> 00:19:32,465
the police and the City Council to look at site needs for drainage, for conservation, and for many other things that were required to get our regulatory permits for this project.

219
00:19:34,097 --> 00:19:54,528
were other special sessions that the city encouraged the team to to go forward with including resiliency planning as the mayor mentioned raising the site up for potential future proofing of this parcel of land it's an emergency facility it needs to be able to respond to the needs of the city we looked at planning

220
00:19:55,128 --> 00:19:58,514
especially for environmental and energy sustainability.

221
00:19:59,256 --> 00:20:08,271
There's now plans in place to put solar panels on the building, as well as the energy efficiencies that we've incorporated into the building.

222
00:20:09,421 --> 00:20:16,006
We looked at site and utility planning, considering that if this site were to flood, what would happen to the utilities on the site?

223
00:20:16,186 --> 00:20:19,129
We located our mechanical rooms on the second floor of the building.

224
00:20:19,529 --> 00:20:27,895
There's been a significant amount of work by all the professionals involved to help to make this a truly state-of-the-art building.

225
00:20:28,736 --> 00:20:35,922
I think along the way we answered just about as many questions about the technological and physical capabilities of the station that could possibly be asked.

226
00:20:36,887 --> 00:20:56,025
The building has the capability to house 130 staff, including a full-size training room, roll call, and physical fitness center, a modern detectives bureau with full evidence storage and processing facility, and an up-to-date flexible holding and processing center for detainees.

227
00:20:57,501 --> 00:21:16,349
Ultimately, we're very happy to see the city make the commitment to building a fossil fuel-free building, as I said, installing solar panels and making the building a leader in energy-efficient design for public safety facilities, which is not easy because these are 24-7 facilities that do use quite a bit of energy compared to other buildings.

228
00:21:17,449 --> 00:21:26,473
These are not goals that are seen in other projects, and we have not seen it in the past, so we truly applaud the city and the mayor and everyone for making this commitment.

229
00:21:27,923 --> 00:21:33,066
Now, seven years later, we believe the city has surpassed what it set out originally to accomplish.

230
00:21:33,426 --> 00:21:37,928
We are excited to begin the final phase of the project, establishing a new home for the police department.

231
00:21:38,348 --> 00:21:38,668
Thank you.

232
00:21:43,271 --> 00:21:43,971
Thank you, Jeff.

233
00:21:44,251 --> 00:21:47,313
And you do feel like a member of the family to all of us, so thank you.

234
00:21:48,253 --> 00:21:51,815
I also want to acknowledge a few more department heads that are present with us today.

235
00:21:51,895 --> 00:21:56,297
We have Alicia Nunley-Benjamin, head of our finance department at City Hall.

236
00:21:56,597 --> 00:21:57,298
Thank you, Alicia.

237
00:21:58,599 --> 00:22:01,161
We have Michael Durham, our veterans agent who's here today.

238
00:22:02,822 --> 00:22:05,984
Our superintendent of schools, Dr. Maurice-Edouard Vincent.

239
00:22:09,527 --> 00:22:11,208
I think, have I missed any other department heads?

240
00:22:12,890 --> 00:22:15,051
Our city engineer, Tim McGivern.

241
00:22:15,291 --> 00:22:17,033
Tim, thank you.

242
00:22:19,835 --> 00:22:26,179
And at this time, I would like to introduce the chief of police, John Jack Buckley.

243
00:22:32,470 --> 00:22:36,594
Thank you, Madam Mayor.

244
00:22:38,435 --> 00:22:41,778
First, not the Madam, but that goes hand-in-hand with the John Jack.

245
00:22:42,719 --> 00:22:46,542
I was born a John and have been Jack since, well, go back to that one.

246
00:22:47,243 --> 00:22:49,525
It's a little bit unfair for me before I officially begin.

247
00:22:50,206 --> 00:22:54,109
I saw that I was put on the bottom of the speaking rolls.

248
00:22:55,831 --> 00:23:04,938
Everyone speaks so eloquently, and I'm new to this, so bear with me, especially if you saw my speech blow away in the wind a couple of minutes ago.

249
00:23:05,519 --> 00:23:07,240
If it's out of order, it's not my fault.

250
00:23:07,501 --> 00:23:12,285
But when the architect comes up and hits a home run in his speech before you, you know you're up against the wall.

251
00:23:13,926 --> 00:23:21,072
Good morning, and thank you all for being here, and for doing your part to bring this building to where we are today.

252
00:23:22,248 --> 00:23:31,340
Today we move from pre-construction to construction, and I cannot wait until we all come back in some 20 months to open the doors to this new police station.

253
00:23:32,642 --> 00:23:37,889
There are many people to thank for this day coming about, but I'd like to begin with my own officers.

254
00:23:39,556 --> 00:23:55,866
The efforts of the Medford Police Patrolmen's Association, Officer Harold McGillivray, and the support of the Medford Police Superior Officer's Association, Sergeant David Bononell, and for many years, Lieutenant Andy Michael Bryan, were the impetus, or should I say push, that got this project rolling.

255
00:23:56,926 --> 00:24:04,431
And I truly thank them for their support, and I thank the members of my police department for bearing with us throughout this time.

256
00:24:05,611 --> 00:24:06,452
The end is in sight.

257
00:24:06,852 --> 00:24:08,053
We will have our building soon.

258
00:24:09,302 --> 00:24:12,363
I also want to give a nod to a special group of officers.

259
00:24:13,783 --> 00:24:30,327
We often speak of the men and women of the Medford Police Department, but in this case, it's the women of this police department that took on a special role to help bring about this day, and I thank them for their loyalty and their hard work.

260
00:24:32,147 --> 00:24:34,908
This past year has been truly amazing for our police department.

261
00:24:35,888 --> 00:24:39,909
Police departments and change are two things that don't often get along.

262
00:24:41,029 --> 00:24:44,430
Yet for the first time in three decades, we have a new police chief.

263
00:24:44,910 --> 00:24:49,592
And now for the first time in almost six decades, we will have a new police station.

264
00:24:51,372 --> 00:24:56,653
I owe a strong debt of gratitude for the support the city has shown our department.

265
00:24:57,614 --> 00:25:00,154
Most importantly, I want to thank Mayor Stephanie Burke.

266
00:25:01,275 --> 00:25:01,735
Mayor Burke,

267
00:25:02,762 --> 00:25:05,703
My officers are truly grateful for your backing of this project.

268
00:25:06,783 --> 00:25:14,366
It wasn't easy, but somehow you pushed us through, and we stand here today to put the first shovels in the ground to a long overdue project.

269
00:25:15,647 --> 00:25:18,128
Your commitment to public safety is noted and appreciated.

270
00:25:19,228 --> 00:25:29,912
You led the process to replace a 28-year legendary police chief, and you guided this department in the city to envision a new future for the community and their police department.

271
00:25:31,899 --> 00:25:33,440
We have a new police station on the way.

272
00:25:34,180 --> 00:25:38,203
You recently purchased new firearms and equipment that were also long overdue.

273
00:25:38,943 --> 00:25:42,445
And you will be providing nine new police vehicles over the next few months.

274
00:25:43,326 --> 00:25:48,369
But most importantly, you've maintained a commitment to advancing this department's community mission.

275
00:25:49,587 --> 00:25:53,611
We have hired 15 to 20 officers since 2016 alone.

276
00:25:53,831 --> 00:26:02,160
And just yesterday, we spoke about hiring up to nine more officers in the very near future to support this building in the community vision.

277
00:26:03,221 --> 00:26:07,866
On a personal note, as the new chief, I want to thank you for your guidance, support, and advice.

278
00:26:09,021 --> 00:26:14,062
You can imagine that replacing a chief who served for three decades can be a daunting task.

279
00:26:14,883 --> 00:26:21,305
You have provided me your lessons learned, having yourself replaced a mayor who served almost three decades before you took office.

280
00:26:22,985 --> 00:26:30,487
You've shown me that once you commit to your job, you do not just own the present and the future, but you own the past.

281
00:26:31,567 --> 00:26:36,529
Regardless of what happened in the past, you learn, you adapt, and you move forward.

282
00:26:37,738 --> 00:26:43,542
I think this building is a great example of those lessons learned and I thank you and our officers.

283
00:26:51,626 --> 00:26:53,768
Yesterday I was on the phone with Chief Sacco.

284
00:26:54,828 --> 00:26:57,750
He too has had a large role in bringing this police station to life.

285
00:26:59,151 --> 00:27:03,334
The chief is hiding out in Florida and could not be here today.

286
00:27:04,174 --> 00:27:06,876
He promises he will be here when we open these doors

287
00:27:07,833 --> 00:27:15,298
And he wants you all to know that he's very happy that that stay is here and he's extremely overjoyed for his officers in this department.

288
00:27:16,439 --> 00:27:22,363
He's also overjoyed knowing this community, which he loves so much, will be getting the police station they deserve.

289
00:27:24,665 --> 00:27:27,787
Take a few moments to acknowledge and thank the city council.

290
00:27:29,521 --> 00:27:33,544
Long before I became chief, I watched those city council meetings every night.

291
00:27:34,405 --> 00:27:35,346
And I know what you went through.

292
00:27:35,366 --> 00:27:37,327
I know the decisions you had to make.

293
00:27:38,008 --> 00:27:38,689
They weren't easy.

294
00:27:39,449 --> 00:27:41,751
And I appreciate you sticking with us and pushing through.

295
00:27:43,052 --> 00:27:43,613
It was tough.

296
00:27:43,973 --> 00:27:45,114
You made some right decisions.

297
00:27:46,565 --> 00:28:02,074
City Council President John Falco, Vice President Brianna Lungokin, Councilor Michael Mox, Councilor Rick Caraviello, Councilor Fred DelaRusso, Councilor Adam Knight, Councilor George Schiapelle, Police Department thanks you for your part in this.

298
00:28:02,715 --> 00:28:06,377
We recognize it and we appreciate your advancement and going forward.

299
00:28:08,408 --> 00:28:11,970
I want to thank Senator Donato, Senator Jalen for your support of policing.

300
00:28:12,630 --> 00:28:15,891
Representative Garberlee and Christine Barber, I thank you.

301
00:28:16,272 --> 00:28:20,253
We're getting used to each other and we'll have long meetings.

302
00:28:21,114 --> 00:28:24,015
District Attorney Marion Ryan, we've had a long relationship.

303
00:28:25,096 --> 00:28:29,458
Your agency works well with the Memphis Police Department.

304
00:28:29,618 --> 00:28:34,200
This station will encourage our relationship moving forward and I thank you.

305
00:28:36,022 --> 00:28:50,133
Jeff Shaw, Elizabeth Appledoom, Alicia Monks, Richard Marks, and Larry McDonough for all the work and for putting up with me, especially in all the changes I make at the last minute.

306
00:28:50,714 --> 00:28:54,717
There's one thing to replace the chief, but I'm not sure they appreciated the changes I made coming in.

307
00:28:56,377 --> 00:29:01,039
I also want to thank a special group of officers who sat with me through these committee meetings.

308
00:29:01,759 --> 00:29:06,181
Captain Kevin Fowler, Captain Barry Clemente, and Lieutenant Jim Colarusso.

309
00:29:06,981 --> 00:29:10,543
Your support is noted and I appreciate it.

310
00:29:11,744 --> 00:29:13,884
If I forget someone, I apologize.

311
00:29:15,345 --> 00:29:16,766
Know that I am grateful to you all.

312
00:29:17,466 --> 00:29:22,148
However, I do need to thank one last person, and this person comes with a remarkable story.

313
00:29:25,540 --> 00:29:29,481
If you haven't met Alva Erickson, take some time to talk to her today.

314
00:29:31,041 --> 00:29:34,782
Alva is my personal secretary, my assistant, and my advisor.

315
00:29:36,442 --> 00:29:38,462
I cannot get through a day without her counsel.

316
00:29:38,882 --> 00:29:41,063
She knows everyone and everything.

317
00:29:41,823 --> 00:29:46,164
She knows more about this department and the history of this department than anyone else.

318
00:29:47,344 --> 00:29:53,445
And for those of you who don't know her story, Alva came to work at the Medford Police Department 60 years ago.

319
00:29:55,095 --> 00:29:55,475
60 years.

320
00:29:56,396 --> 00:30:03,062
She sat through this same process of planning, groundbreaking, and opening the doors to that building behind us.

321
00:30:13,192 --> 00:30:16,695
Alba will have worked in all three police stations once we open up.

322
00:30:17,336 --> 00:30:18,136
She has seen it all.

323
00:30:19,244 --> 00:30:24,451
HBO could pull her in and do their own miniseries on the things she knows and the stories she tells.

324
00:30:27,255 --> 00:30:31,701
Alva, I'd like to give you these items and ask that you help break the ground today.

325
00:30:31,921 --> 00:30:32,422
It's only fair.

326
00:31:04,019 --> 00:31:05,860
And I mean, it takes some time to talk to Alvin.

327
00:31:05,900 --> 00:31:08,462
She knows everything.

328
00:31:09,423 --> 00:31:11,364
So this building is good for the police department.

329
00:31:12,185 --> 00:31:13,266
That goes without saying.

330
00:31:14,407 --> 00:31:17,589
It will bring us into the 21st century and beyond.

331
00:31:19,230 --> 00:31:25,535
All new equipment, all the modern tools, a clean, friendly environment, and we thank you all for that.

332
00:31:26,977 --> 00:31:29,879
But most importantly, this building will become a pillar of our community.

333
00:31:30,459 --> 00:31:40,727
We will open the doors to a modern police station that is inviting to the public, evokes confidence in the community and the police partnership we work so hard to foster.

334
00:31:42,828 --> 00:31:50,654
The MPD community soon will flourish and be the center of our relationships, our openness and our commitment to all those who make Medford their home.

335
00:31:51,715 --> 00:31:54,777
When it's all said and done, we will have that new police station,

336
00:31:55,782 --> 00:32:01,464
but this building will stand as a monument to the public partnership our city will have with its community.

337
00:32:03,164 --> 00:32:06,265
You should all be proud that you had a part in that.

338
00:32:06,285 --> 00:32:08,766
I personally thank each and every one of you.

339
00:32:09,706 --> 00:32:10,026
Thank you.

340
00:32:23,072 --> 00:32:27,879
Congratulations, you really are amazing and you are the heart and soul of this police department.

341
00:32:27,919 --> 00:32:30,843
So thank you for everything you've done and being a part of this today.

342
00:32:36,704 --> 00:32:41,425
At this time I'd like to invite Father Robert Casey to conclude the ceremony with a convocation.

343
00:32:41,445 --> 00:32:47,007
Oh God, builder of all things, you have placed on all of us the obligation of toil and work.

344
00:32:47,547 --> 00:32:56,129
Grant that the work we begin as we break ground on the new Medford Police Headquarters may serve to better the lives of all the citizens of Medford.

345
00:32:56,769 --> 00:32:59,030
Watch over all who take on this work.

346
00:32:59,670 --> 00:33:07,513
And when it is completed, may it be a source of pride and accomplishment for all who planned it, built it, and occupy it.

347
00:33:08,253 --> 00:33:11,755
Bless Chief Jack Buckley and the members of the Medford Police Department.

348
00:33:12,075 --> 00:33:17,437
Watch over them, keep them safe, and always guide them to be respectful to all they serve.

349
00:33:17,897 --> 00:33:19,538
We ask this in God's name.

350
00:33:20,118 --> 00:33:20,418
Amen.

351
00:33:24,453 --> 00:33:26,034
Thank you everybody for joining us.

352
00:33:26,054 --> 00:33:27,375
We're now going to kick it over there.

353
00:33:57,945 --> 00:33:59,007
Thank you.

